annotation.TEXT: Alright, it looks like it's time for phase 4 of the boss fight! What's his true form gonna be?

BGM: Knuckles Chaotix - Marina Madness
I'm being a bit cautious for suddenly-appearing saws now. Also, I saw him launch Sumo Bro. fire at the beginning of the fight, but I haven't seen that attack again yet.
Yep, I've completed the Special World, so let me through!
Oh, man. It looks like sunset here. Hmm... Are there supposed to be orange squares surrounding those lower level dots there?

Yeah, that was a good fight, Ballser. It's nice to see that you're being a really good sport about this. So, maybe we'll meet again in "Something even more else" (or whatever yogui decides to call the sequel to this game, if he makes one).
Hmm... Something tells me I'm not quite done yet!
I'll take that as a "yes"!
Yep, as I thought, those are stun quakes he's causing when he lands.
...I guess not. So, let's take this warp star then! ...Let me guess... It'll take me back to the beginning of the game, just like the warp star after Funky in the original SMW.
Hello, and welcome to the finale of Something else! Alright, it's finally time to wrap this up! Let's see just who this "Someone" is! (Hint: It's not me, though that would've been funny.)
Oh, man! Am I done?
"Tick." Graze +1.
Hey, Luigi... You might want to check your hat and clothes for holes...

Alright, it's true final boss time!
This place appears to be using a darker shade of green now.

The main island on the right has turned pink now.

BGM: CUSTOM - The Final Phase - Total Rocked Out Edition by Masashi27
Alright, let's head to Bonus and see what's beyond that invisible barrier that wouldn't let me through until I beat the Special World...
Okay, so he's just walking back and forth shooting out Gordos horizontally. That's pretty easy to deal with, but I'm sure it'll get harder!
Whoa, that was kind of close...
The music stopped, but... The Evil Guy is still here, and he wants more power! ARR! ARR! ARR!

Okay, that went well, but I have a feeling that I'm not done yet... (Unless this game pulls another "banana" on me...)

At least the fireballs are coming out a regular predictable intervals. Now, if only the parakoopas would come out at regular intervals...
Oh, hey there, The Evil Guy. How's it going?
Bye, Yoshi!
...Yep, I was right! And the overworld palette has even changed, too! So, does that mean...
Let's just keep dodging those hands with popsicle power and tossing these little balls back at The Evil Ballser Guy, or whatever he's called.
Well, I guess that's that, but before I end the video, I'm going to walk around the overworld and show what each map looks like with the changed palette.
FLAWLESS VICTORY.

Whoa! Okay, that didn't exactly work, but at least I didn't get burned.

Finally! Oh, and while they may appear to be blue-colored (or gray-colored, or bluish-gray-colored), these koopduders actually act like green parakoopas.

I wonder how many more hits this'll take, and I wonder if this auto-scrolling area has an end, or if it'll continue looping endlessly until one of us is defeated...
Whoa, who's that guy?
ROUND 3... FIGHT!!!

Alright, so now The Evil Ballser Guy is showing his nasty teeth, and I was given a peach (not a popsicle?) right there, and it looks like I've gotta chuck parakoopas' shells at him now while dodging the other stuff he spits out.

FLAWLESS VICTORY.

All those skulls... Also, a 1-up cake, a doughnut, and a popsicle. And, just like usual, I'll eat the popsicle last, because I once again think that it'll be more useful than fireballs.
I think this MOOOONNN might be a slightly darker color now.
Another close call there, though I probably won't do a slow-motion instant replay for that one.

And thus concludes the overworld tour! Well, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Something else! I may do a bonus episode involving Else Castle 3 if it turns out that there are rooms there that I haven't visited (since I'm told the disco doors send you to random rooms). Also, if there are any levels you want me to TAS, let me know!

Okay, it looks like we actually are going to have another phase to this boss fight! (Unless their fused form is just a banana or something...)

So, I've unlocked a warp star. Is there anywhere else I can go around here? (Not counting this glitchy path, which I've been told is actually already fixed, and it's only present here because I started this save file on an older version that had the glitch.)
FLAWLESS VICTORY.
Hi, Yoshi!
